				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">One caveat with using standards is that very few retro console actually followed the standards 100%. Go ahead, anyone name a retro NTSC machine besides the Amiga that outputs exactly 60000/1001 Hz vertical refresh rate, for example. I would very much doubt the NES outputs the exact line length that the standard calls for.</div>

