						<div class="postbody">The NES PPU line period is 341 pixels. The standard NTSC line period is 341.25 NES pixels. But as I view it, the length of the active picture portion is what matters.
<br />
<br />The magnifying glass size is less than a pixel off, and as I said, it's a case of round-to-nearest-tile anyway.</div>

