					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I spent most of the evening testing various games in the NES library. 280 and 282 seem to be the most common expected ratios. For example, the silver ball in "Pinbot" becomes perfectly round via 280x240, whereas the bumpers in "Pinball" lean more towards 282x240 for perfect roundness.
<br />
<br />I did find one extreme case in "Wheel of Fortune". I don't know if the programmers expected the wheel to appear perfectly round, but it requires 292x240 to make it that way. It's the most anamorphic design of graphics I've seen yet in an NES game.</div>

