						<div class="postbody">The wiki entry:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Overscan" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Overscan</a>
<br />
<br />Claims the NES PAR on a 4:3 TV to be 1.143, which would make the 256x240 area equal to 274x240. This seems quite a bit less than the 280~282 we've been finding in most games. Am I misunderstanding that article? I wish whoever wrote it would have clarified in a much more simple way what aspect formula should be used for the 256x240 active area...</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

